    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102654</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">ShortAnswerResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>One batch of gray paint is made with 5 cups of white paint and 3 cups of black paint.</p>

<ol>
	<li>Draw a diagram representing 1&#xA0;batch of gray paint.</li>
	<li>How many cups of white and black paint are needed for four batches?</li>
	<li>How many cups of white and black paint are needed for <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="14">\(\frac13\)</span> of a batch?</li>
	<li>Explain why all of these mixtures of paint will make the same shade of gray.</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>Answers vary. Sample response:
	<p><img class="h-max-height--7-lines" src="/image_files/30675.png" /></p>
	</li>
	<li>12 cups black and 20 cups white</li>
	<li>
<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="14">\(\frac13\)</span> cup black and <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="11218">\(\frac53\)</span> cup white</li>
	<li>They are all different numbers of batches of the same paint recipe. The ratios of white paint to black paint in these mixtures are equivalent.</li>
</ol>
</div>
